  <summary>11/21/2003--Introduced.
Commission on Preemptive Foreign Policy and Military Planning Act - Establishes the Commission on Preemptive Foreign Policy and Military Planning to: (1) review the doctrine of preemption adopted by the President in the National Security Strategy of the United States of America of September 2002; and (2) assess the consequences and implications of the doctrine for foreign policy and military planning.</summary>
